<subSubSection id="737E49D3544F277DFB1AFC5312963931" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="note">
<paragraph id="7024518B81A64842CE850632BF6A968C" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F000CDDCD0A2547F7D50F78301479989" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
The only species known from the Guianas that would agree with 
<normalizedToken id="E38DE9485485497D02F992E1DECD69FA" originalValue="Meyer’s">Meyer's</normalizedToken>
description is 
<taxonomicName id="95B62F0FD7D7EC2AF3F1425FEE0FCCA4" authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis id="6A10AB4397DFB116D09B272DC15DEB89" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Euploca humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="BD979F709ED477D154E4EF16710D69A1" author="Foerther, H" journalOrPublisher="Sendtnera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="35 - 241" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" refId="B15" refString="Foerther, H, 1998. Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae). Sendtnera 5: 35 - 241, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" title="Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" volume="5" year="1998">
<normalizedToken id="11C5928739185BF717C524583761F0B6" originalValue="Förther">Foerther</normalizedToken>
(1998
</bibRefCitation>
: 238) lists 
<taxonomicName id="8015ACF11097C59612CC82C46D812AF1" authority="L., 1774" authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Messerschmidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Messerschmidia incana" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incana">
<emphasis id="D1165C37FC404BF17E3A4638840C0E2B" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Messerschmidia incana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4FB50F053E60E963C2A082D860794516" authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium ternatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ternatum">
<emphasis id="EF93C483BBC946164353020D3B605CE3" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Heliotropium ternatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="D21901D4D910C4B52F6FC2D5BC949D9A" authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis id="ED0C91DF4541B1FA9A84AC578E074D31" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Euploca humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] with a question mark, but Meyer placed a synonym in the protolog of his new species, 
<taxonomicName id="474ED4F5AEA0C78783C470D91FD9FCD0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tournefortia sessilifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilifolia">
<emphasis id="56C1347095C702B52D98F6093D09CC00" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Tournefortia sessilifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. (1804: 360), a species described from Argentina. Because 
<taxonomicName id="E978AAEF6F36C093EA4988F1D6589E9D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="sessilifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilifolia">
<emphasis id="4BC0FF1F1B92DFAD4E66A5B41D5B66F5" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">sessilifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was available in 
<taxonomicName id="9E5BD126E1AA12337D690FB2FDC639AE" authority="L., 1774" authorityName="L." authorityYear="1774" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Messerschmidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Messerschmidia" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AF5E1CFBD45E044A41706C80C17ABD97" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Messerschmidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it should have been used as the epithet. Therefore the name by Meyer is not validly published.
</paragraph>
